 \X/                                                                       \X/
 /X\ In Distance Between Dreams, the most historic year in big wave surfing/X\ 
 \X/ comes to life through the eyes of iconic surfer Ian Walsh, as he sets \X/
 /X\ mind and body in motion to redefine the upper limits of what's        /X\
 \X/ considered ærideable.' With massive El Ni±o powered swells building   \X/
 /X\ across the Pacific, Ian, Shaun, D.K. and Luke Walsh band together in  /X\
 \X/ a way that only brothers can to progress surfing to unimaginable      \X/
 /X\ heights.                                                              /X\
 \X/                                                                       \X/
 /X\ Big wave surfing's transition from jet ski assists to paddling in     /X\
 \X/ raises the stakes, putting Walsh's intense physical and mental        \X/
 /X\ training, the latest technology, swell modeling, and safety team, his /X\
 \X/ brothers, to the ultimate test. Surfers John John Florence, Greg Long,\X/
 /X\ Shane Dorian and more link up with Walsh as he rides an emotional     /X\
 \X/ rollercoaster through this momentous winter.                          \X/
 /X\                                                                       /X\
 \X/ The second feature in Red Bull Media House's The Unrideables          \X/
 /X\ franchise, Distance Between Dreams invites viewers right into the     /X\
 \X/ heart of the action with first person perspective, state-of-the-art   \X/
 /X\ cinematography, and captivating sound. Through unprecedented access,  /X\
 \X/ prepare to truly experience Walsh's quest to survive and thrive in    \X/
 /X\ one of the most hostile environments on earth.                        /X\
 \X/                                                                       \X/
 /X\ RiP NOTES: Top big wave surfing documentary film that u must watch!   /X\
